parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS module can cause the brakes to lock up or fail, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS light flashes at startup
the rear brake pedal locks up
the front brake lever is hard to apply
the front brake lever freezes up
the brake pedal goes down and hits the floorboard without any braking pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic throttle can cause the motorcycle to suddenly lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and potentially fatal consequences.
symptoms: the engine continues to run but the motorcycle slows down to around 5 mph
the motorcycle ceases to respond to throttle input
sudden loss of power while accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pump can cause the engine to overheat, leading to premature wear, damage, or even engine seizure, which can result in accidents or leave the rider stranded.
symptoms: a knocking noise is coming from the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause damage to engine components, lead to premature wear, or even engine seizure, which can result in accidents or leave the rider stranded.
symptoms: a knocking noise is coming from the engine
